Sam Chalmers, son of 1990 Grand Slam legend Craig, has been using his own lamentable story to warn teams at the IRB Junior World Championship in New Zealand about the dangers of taking drugs.

Chalmers, 20, tested positive for a banned substance in the run up to last year’s tournament in France and was subsequently banned for two years.

The Melrose player has expressed his regret at his mistake and told his tale to this year’s future stars of world rugby and encouraged them to be aware and educate themselves on anti-doping matters.

