Chalmers has since gone on to become a personal trainer and will be eligible to play Rugby again from June 2015.

‘You don’t realise how much you miss something until you lose it,’ said the former Melrose player. ‘I now know that hard work beats everything, and there’s no shortcuts in Rugby.

'All the players that have gone pro have worked hard. I cheated and took the easy option, but you can’t do it as it will come back to bite you.

‘I was under pressure to get bigger and one day I decided to take what my friend had taken. I didn’t think what it could do to my body.

'It was a supplement that I ordered online and I only took it for a week, but that online order was the worst mistake of my life.’

